    "description": "This PR applies some minor fixes to allow drawing lines in VR to work on Windows, and allows compilation of Cython modules for a Python 3/Windows setup.\r\n\r\nWindows has alloca in a different header file from other systems, which we were previously handling using Cython-based preprocessor directives. For reasons that are still not fully clear to me, this is buggy on Windows when using Python 3. I've gotten around this by moving the preprocessor logic to a C header file, which I think is a more portable solution anyway.\r\n\r\nIn volume rendering, the line drawing function in Cython specifically takes int64 ndarrays for index parameters. The changes I've made simply enforce this type for these arrays. This fixes a set of Windows test failures.\r\n\r\nThe FancyURLOpener change is a Python 2/3 fix.\r\n\r\nUPDATE: Found and fixed more Python 2/3 issues in `plot_container`. ",
